From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] debug: replace k_msleep with k_busy_wait in main

Patch 0026 inserted k_msleep(100) between 2a and 2b. Even with that
sleep, 2b never appears. So either:
  a) k_msleep itself hangs (kernel timer / scheduler problem)
  b) printk for 2b blocks even after the sleep

Replace k_msleep with k_busy_wait, which spins in CPU busy-loop
without going through the kernel timer subsystem. If 2b shows up,
the kernel timer was the culprit. If still no 2b, the problem is
in the printk / CDC path itself.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
@@ -160,7 +160,7 @@ int main(void)
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2a_pre_led_start\n");

     /* patch 0025: bypass led_start() to isolate hang */
-    k_msleep(100);
+    k_busy_wait(100000);
     err = 0;
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2b_post_led_start err=%d\n", err);
     if (err) {
